# Dataset Information

## Dataset

**BPI Challenge 2016 – Customer Complaints**

This dataset originates from the **Business Process Intelligence (BPI) Challenge 2016** and contains customer complaint records from the Dutch Employee Insurance Agency (UWV). It is widely used for process mining education and research.

The dataset included in this repository (`BPI2016_Complaints.csv`) was used to perform process discovery and analysis in **Celonis**, followed by process redesign in **SAP Signavio**.

---

## Dataset Structure

The dataset contains **18 attributes** describing customer complaints, including:

| Column | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| CustomerID | Unique customer identifier |
| ComplaintDossierID | Complaint case identifier |
| ComplaintID | Individual complaint identifier |
| ContactDate | Date the complaint was recorded |
| AgeCategory | Customer age group |
| Gender | Customer gender |
| Office_U / Office_W | Internal office identifiers |
| ContactChannelID | Communication channel used |
| ComplaintTheme / ComplaintSubtheme / ComplaintTopic | Complaint classification |
| ComplaintTheme_EN / ComplaintSubtheme_EN / ComplaintTopic_EN | English translations of the complaint categories |

The complaint themes include topics such as payment delays, incorrect information, missed appointments, communication issues, and document processing.

---

## Project Usage

The dataset was imported into **Celonis Process Mining** to:

- Discover the existing complaint handling process.
- Analyze process variants and case behavior.
- Identify process inefficiencies and improvement opportunities.
- Support the redesign of the workflow using **SAP Signavio (BPMN 2.0)**.

---

## Notes

Although the dataset provides rich complaint information, the event log contains only a single recorded activity per complaint case. This limits end-to-end process analysis, making throughput times and waiting periods unobservable. These limitations were considered during the redesign of the complaint handling process.
